{\*\xmlclose}. And there was very little in my parents\rquote  background which would have led me to any political commitment or sociological commitment, or social commitment. My father was a businessman who had arrived from 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Lithuania{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} in the wave o
f immigration in the twenties and thirties. My mother was more interestingly different, in that she was ... from a Polish family, but was actually just born in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}South Africa{\*\xmlclose}, and then went to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Law{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, after having gro
