d left school, I had already a vague social justice commitment, in relation to South Africa. I had certainly a vague idea ... of Zionism, that I would end up in Israel. A
nd I think I did have ... well, I must have, I had a sense of wanting to do something to help. You know, this was a very strong kind of humanitarian impulse rather than a political impulse, which is why I actually did social work, which was an odd choice,
