d
 I threw myself into my academic work, you know, the reading was interesting, and seemed to me easy, and the sociological part became more and more interesting, but so did the social work part. You know, I was surrounded by stimuli. And that was the point
, I think, where, in those four years, where part of your identity involves either shedding previous commitments, or trying to integrate them into some way, or being more aware of the contradictions. 
