s an important figure to mention, because she now is the wife of Thabo Mbeki, the President of South Africa. S
he Africanised her name from Mary to Zanele afterwards. When I came to London and started working as a social worker, she came soon afterwards, and worked in the same place as I did and we stayed in contact. And then she went to Zambia, and we lost contac
t. Then she got married to Thabo, so she\rquote s now the President\rquote s wife. I\rquote ve always wanted to look her up and say, \'93Look, do you remember ...\'94 but I\rquote ve always been embarrassed by it. 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\sa200\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid10315610\contextualspace {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid6313845\charrsid13831242 
