. And so I think ... in the clearest way, the simple idea of labelling theory, and the anti-authoritarianism that I picked up from the LSE sit-in days, and the spirit of, you know, the excitement of being anti-auth
ority, reinforced for me the idea that I could find some connection between political commitment and intellectual life, which was one of the sixties themes that emerged \u8722\'2d bearing all the myths, or problems, that we later saw. 
