up and changing into my respectable gear to go and interview magistrates! I was, literally, changing identity. You know, I got that chameleon sense of social reality very dramatically from that, you know, because I saw how I was being treated. That was th
e time it hit me, how important the external image was ... Because if I was dressed like a kid, and I had long hair with long sideburns, and obviously I wasn\rquote 
t 16, but I was only 23 or 24, so I looked young. And when I came with an anorak ... to the caf\'e9, it was obviously very different when, later on in the afternoon, I came into the same caf\'e9
