position as a teacher in a university, all these gelled together, and you were looking for integration. And now, not that I accept the label in any way, I think the post-modernist insistence on some form of fragmentation is actually much more realistic, i
n the sense that those worlds just don\rquote t cohere. It is very hard to find a master political analogy, and then a master epistemological one, and it\rquote 
