, self-righteous saying, I was sort of putting aside all this frivolous life in England, and I was going to go, you know, fight the real battle where blood and thunder were running. And he was a bit sceptical about that! And also thought, from the beginni
ng, correctly, that the situation in Israel was much worse than I thought it was, and that there was much less room for doing good and much }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid6313845\charrsid11558009 more}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\insrsid6313845\charrsid13831242  compromising to do. He was much more radical about it, whereas I was rather smug and satisfied about it, and cri
ticising him and others, implicitly, for this, having the good life, while I was sacrificing myself. You know, that\rquote 
s exaggerating it a bit. So we had a few bitter interchanges about that. But then, gradually, as my criticism of Israel became more, more radical, I saw how correct he was!
