t really excluded. And as the years went by, and I got more, more visible, politically, especially after I started working on torture, my exclusion was much more deliberate. At first, it was just like any outsider not getting into a subculture. Afterwards
, it became much more deliberate. So at the work level, I didn\rquote t find stimulus. I found the students appalling.
