What is the impact, then, of those texts? Not just what goes on into socially constructing them, but what is the impact? Which means a series of sub-questions. Many sub-questions! Some which I didn\rquote 
t have the tools to answer. Sub-question number one might be yours, which is, why do some people react completely differently to others? Sub-question number two is,
