as doing a study, and they showed that there was some overlap in commitments. I\rquote m the kind of sociologist for whom those big issues are important. Because I do other work myself doesn\rquote t mean I think those questions aren\rquote 
t important. On the contrary, I\rquote m just amazed that the people who have got the methodological tools are wasting their potential by not asking these important questions. 
