t represent the starving African, the African child coming to the clinic being fed. This is \'93disempowering\'94 or \'93negative imagery\'94 becau
se you must talk about empowerment. The political correctness movement has hit at all these organisations, and so in the leaflet, they won\rquote t talk about compassion and starvation, and they won\rquote t talk about the poor people, they\rquote 
ll talk about \'93project partners\'94, and so on.
