\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\insrsid6313845\charrsid13831242 Stan:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid6313845\charrsid13831242 Part, yeah. Oh yeah. But also, I think, some of my own illness [Parkinson\rquote s Disease] has opened my e
yes up to some wider dangers and wider prospects in a society, which lead, you know, lead me to conclusions which I might have shied away from before. But I think it\rquote 
s a difficult one to explain. Sometimes, as one gets older, some things look a bit more ambiguous and furry, and that\rquote s, that is still true. But then other things look as if they require a radically clear position, and that you shouldn\rquote 
t fudge it. So it\rquote s a mixture, it\rquote s a complicated mixture, and I think the illness does play some part in it, because I think it\rquote s often very mood driven.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\insrsid6313845\charrsid13831242 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid6313845\charrsid13831242 But, now, you mentioned a couple more people just then, but are there any other people that we haven
\rquote t talked about?
\par 
