\rquote m fed up with modern cinema. As Ruth will tell you, I won\rquote t go to most movies. I like a cheerful movie, I won\rquote t go to a movie that I haven\rquote t seen before. I\rquote 
m just not prepared to waste time on rubbish. So my greatest, my greatest enjoyment is going out for dinner and sitting and talking to friends. I feel really privileged that, that I can go to New York, and I can go to Oslo, and I can go to Paris, and I
\rquote ll find a subculture of people, largely who worked either in the criminology or Human Rights. So I feel extraordinarily lucky in having excellent people, who are good companions, who one can discuss pol
itical things with, and personal things. Yeah. So I would have no hesitation about that one.
